## Analysis
- **Allocations**: No change (18-31 allocs/op)
- **Memory**: Slight increase for LargeValue (+7KB due to value copy)
- **Time**: Mostly similar, some slight improvements in Get operations

## Conclusion
The response pooling saves 1 Response allocation per operation, but we had to add 1 allocation
to copy the value data in Get operations (since we can't return pooled memory to the caller).
Net effect on allocation count is zero, but there may be small GC pressure reduction since
Response structs are reused. The time improvements are marginal and within noise.

**Recommendation**: This optimization has minimal impact when used alone. It would be more
effective combined with other optimizations (especially if we can avoid the value copy by
using a different pooling strategy).
